Here is a possible implementation in Julia:

```julia-repl
abstract type AbstractVehicle end;
struct Car <: AbstractVehicle end;
struct Motorcycle <: AbstractVehicle end;
struct Bus <: AbstractVehicle end;
struct Truck <: AbstractVehicle end;

ispersonal(::Union{Car,Motorcycle}) = true 
ispersonal(::Union{Bus,Truck}) = false 
ispersonal(::AbstractVehicle) = false

# Examples:
ispersonal(Car()) # returns true 
ispersonal(Motorcycle()) # returns true 
ispersonal(Bus()) # returns false
```

This function will work for types `Car`, `Motorcycle`, `Bus` and `Truck`. The function has a default return value of `false` for any other subtype of `AbstractVehicle`.
